description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit a highly motivated and dedicated Driver to join our Driving Team based at Carlisle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will need to possess a full driving licence and have a good local knowledge. Basic computer skills and a confident telephone manner are also a requirement. Flexibility and the ability to communicate effectively as part of a team are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is an average 16.375 hours per week / 196.5 hours over a 12 week rota and will include a mixture of evenings, weekends and night shifts. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing date for all applications will be Sunday 15th November 2020.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interviews will be remote and take place on Wednesday 25th November 2020.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We expect a high level of interest in this post and may close the vacancy early if we have received sufficient applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants will only be shortlisted if they can clearly demonstrate in the supporting information their suitability for the post in relation to the attached job description and person specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
